Mehdija Šekić

About me

I was born (27.06.2001) and have completed primary school in Sanski Most and electrical engineering high school in Bihać. After completing secondary education, I enrolled in college in Mostar. I am currently in my final year of the Faculty of Information Technologies.



I have ability to learn quickly, listen and communicate with others, correctly and motivated, ease of analyzing and solving problems. I am adaptable, and a teamwork player. In general I am an optimistic,energetic and positive person.



I love to travel and explore, play social games and meet new people.I enjoy playing chess, listening to music, working out and playing team and indidual quizzes.



Programming Languages: C++ and C#: Gained proficiency in high school and continued to develop skills during my faculty studies. Java: Acquired independently to enhance qualifications for a Java instructor position. Full-Stack Web Development: Angular and .NET: Successfully designed and implemented a full-stack web application for a furniture web shop as a pivotal project during my academic tenure. Web Technologies: React: Mastered through a combination of an internship experience and self-learning, including watching a comprehensive Udemy course. Demonstrated competence through asynchronous collaboration on assigned tasks.
